                  br
                  br
                p Want to learn how to code? Want to make interactive installations? Already slinging for loops around, but need refinement or help with a new project? Take our <a href="http://processing.org" target="_blank">Processing</a> class.
                p The class meets every Thursday from 6 - 7pm at the studio, <a href='https://maps.google.com/maps?q=1201+Mazant+St,+New+Orleans,+LA&sll=29.966471,-90.033884&hl=en&ie=UTF8&hq=&hnear=1201+Mazant+St,+New+Orleans,+Louisiana+70117&ll=29.966554,-90.034094&spn=0.001764,0.002631&t=m&z=19&vpsrc=0&iwloc=A' target='_blank')>1201 Mazant</a>. Class will start the Thursday after Mardi Gras, March 6th.
                br
                strong Watch the video to learn more
                  span.glyphicon.glyphicon-chevron-right
                br
                br
                a(data-toggle='collapse', data-target='#processing-about') What is Processing?
                .col-sm-12.visible-xs
                  br
                  br
              .col-sm-6
                iframe(src="//player.vimeo.com/video/80274630?title=0&amp;byline=0&amp;portrait=0", width="100%", height="250px", frameborder="0", webkitallowfullscreen mozallowfullscreen allowfullscreen)
                a(href="http://vimeo.com/80274630") 1. HELLO</a> from <a href="http://vimeo.com/shiffman">shiffman</a> on <a href="https://vimeo.com">Vimeo</a>.</p>.
            .row
              #processing-about.collapse.col-sm-8.col-sm-offset-2
                br
                p Processing is a programming language, development environment, and online community. Since 2001, Processing has promoted software literacy within the visual arts and visual literacy within technology. <strong>Initially created to serve as a software sketchbook and to teach computer programming fundamentals within a visual context</strong>, Processing evolved into a development tool for professionals. Today, there are tens of thousands of students, artists, designers, researchers, and hobbyists who use Processing for learning, prototyping, and production (quoted from <a href='http://processing.org' target="_blank">processing.org</a>).
